summary: Disney reveals Captain Marvel character during Marvel Day at Sea
title: Disney reveals Captain Marvel character during Marvel Day at Sea
body:
We got our first look today at the Captain Marvel character that will be meeting guests during the Disney Cruise Line’s Marvel Day at Sea event. Disney also announced that Captain Marvel will also be coming to select Disney theme parks around the world, including  Disney California Adventure park, Disneyland Paris and Shanghai Disney Resort!

Disney also announced a new #HigherFurtherFaster campaign they are launching in 2019 that will feature a variety of cross-promotions for Captain Marvel, including Hasbro, Funko, LEGO, Invicta, Stance, Diff, Bioworld, Fast Forward, Her Universe, Jaya, C-Life and Mad Engine.

There will also be exclusive Captain Marvel merchandise available at shopDisney.

Marvel will also be releasing new Captain Marvel material that will provide a backstory to the upcoming film. There will also be video game tie-ins on Marvel’s console, mobile, and PC games.

Captain Marvel hits theaters on March 8, 2019!

Be sure to follow us on Twitter and Facebook for the latest news, photos and more from Disney!
